<br>
We got rained out last night. Showed up at 8am like we were told. No body at the fields but players, where the guys holding the tourney were I don't know. Some guy drove by on his way to work and told everybody that they called him last night postponing the tourney till next Sunday. Basically we were really upset to drive 2 hours or more, end up 2-0 with a shot to win the whole thing. Spend our hard earned money on the tourney and motel rooms so the directors could no show us on Sun. I don't know what the weather did we went home immediately. But the fields would have been playable by 10am IMHO. <br>
<br>
If you get rained out that is one thing. But the way we were treated is flat horrible. I know these are college kids, but come on. I bet there are severals teams who will never go back. Mine included.<br>
<br>
Then again I guess the guy at the park could have been giving out bum info but at that point we didn't care. <br>
<br>
It was bad enough. The umpires not giving a rip or knowing the rules. Then you have 1:30 minutes between games. Then waiting on the umpires for an extra 10 minutes to decide which field they were going to take. But to show up at the ballpark at 11pm when you couldn't play and then to get back at park at 8am with nobody around. As you can tell I was a little worked up. <br>
<br>
When I hold a tourney I get cell #'s of coaches so if something happens I can reach them. And do my best to see everyone gets there money's worth. And that is the way I expect to be treated.<br>
<br>
The only thing that makes me somewhat happy is that we paid our entry fee by check. IF you know what I mean.<br>
<br>
Sorry I have babbled long enough.<br>
<br>
